# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Darling — environment variable template
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. Copy this file to ".env"        ->  cp .env.example .env
#   2. Replace every placeholder below with your real values.
#   3. Never commit ".env" — it is already listed in .gitignore.
#
# WHERE TO FIND THESE (Supabase dashboard):
#   Project Settings -> API
#     - "Project URL"                  -> SUPABASE_URL
#     - "Project API keys" -> anon/public -> SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#     - "Project API keys" -> service_role -> SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
#
# ⚠️  SECURITY:
#   - SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_ANON_KEY are safe to expose in the browser
#     ONLY because Row Level Security (RLS) protects your tables. Turn RLS on.
#   - SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY bypasses RLS. Use it ONLY on a server / build
#     step. NEVER ship it to the front-end and NEVER commit it.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Public values (used by the browser via config.js)
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-public-anon-key

# Backend / build-step only — do NOT expose to the browser
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-secret-service-role-key
